{
  "text": "The study of the structure of birational maps between two Mori fiber spaces is one of the most interesting open problems in 3-fold birational geometry. In recent years a lot of progress has been made in this direction especially since the introduction of the Sarkisov program by Corti, Reid and Sarkisov [CITATION_1] [Cor-Rei00]. The aim of this program is to factor any birational map between two Mori fiber spaces as the composition of simpler maps called elementary links. Each link is composed of flips, inverse flips and divisorial contractions. In this context it is important to understand such birational maps. The structure of divisorial contractions is still unknown in its complete generality, even though lately a lot of progress has been made in this direction by Corti, Cutkosky, Kawamata, Kawakita, Mori,Tziolas and others.",
